All reagents were of analytical grade and purchased from FUJIFILM Wako Pure Chemical ( Osaka , Japan ), except for anthranilic acid which was purchased from Kanto Chemical ( Tokyo , Japan ). Unless otherwise stated, all organic solvents were distilled prior to use. CHROMATOREX PSQ 100B silica gel (Fuji Silysia Chemical, Aichi , Japan ) was used for silica gel column chromatography. TLC Silica gel 60 F 254 glass plate (Merck, Darmstadt, Germany ) was used for TLC analyses. The TLC plate was developed with solvent mixture of MeOH–CHCl 3 –AcOH (15:5:1) for 1 and n -hexane–EtOAc (10:1) for 2 (see the section
Isolation and quantification of fluorescent compounds
). The spots were detected under UV light ( 365 nm ), and further by heating after dipping the plate with 20% phosphomolybdic acid in EtOH.

All statistical analyses were performed with R version 4.1.2 ( R Core Team, 2021 ). Significant differences among three plant species were tested by one-way analyses of variance (ANOVA), using the multcomp package. The analysis employed the AUCEm as a dependent variable and the plant species as an independent variable. The ANOVA was followed by a Tukey–Kramer post-hoc analysis to test the pairwise comparisons. The unpaired t -test was used to test the significant difference between two plant species in the behavioral assay and colorimetry;
p <
0.05 was considered statistically significant. The boxplot in Fig. 2 was depicted using the ggplot2 package. For effect sizes, we computed the standardized mean difference expressed as Hedge’ s g using the compute.es package.
